        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 1:39PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 139 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hempstead, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Navasota, Hempstead, Prairie View, Pine Island, Todd Mission, and
Plantersville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
